{{Infobox person | name = Linda Seger | image = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = American | yearsactive = 1981–present | occupation = [[author]], [[educator]], [[screenwriter]], [[consultant]] | known_for = ''Making a Good Script Great: A Guide for Writing & Rewriting'' }} ''' Linda Seger ''' is a screenwriting instructor and screenplay consultant, best known for contributions to films like ''[[Braindead (film)|Braindead]]'' and ''[[Universal Soldier (1992 film)|Universal Soldier]]'', as well as popular seminars on screenwriting.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0103873/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_wr#writers</ref> Seger is the author of several books on the subject of screenwriting, including ''Making a Good Script Great: A Guide for Writing & Rewriting'', ''Creating Unforgettable Characters: Practical Guide to Character Development in Films, TV Series, Advertisements, Novels and Short Stories'' and ''The Art of Adaptation: Turning Fact and Fiction into Film''.<ref>https://us.macmillan.com/author/lindaseger/</ref><ref>http://mwp.com/author-book/dr-linda-seger/</ref>
==Career== Seger began her script consultancy in 1981, basing it on a method she had developed for her doctoral dissertation project.<ref>https://www.lindaseger.com/script-consultant-screenwriting-coach/</ref><ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105698/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm</ref> Since then, she has consulted on over 2,000 scripts including over 50 produced feature films and over 35 produced television projects.<ref>http://www.scriptmag.com/features/the-great-linda-seger-has-done-it-again</ref>
